  <section>
    <h2>Characteristics</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Combines the best of digital and paper. You can write freely by hand on paper, then transfer your notes into a digital structure for storage.</li>
      <li>Secure and flexible. All data belongs to the user and is stored locally in popular formats (md, txt). Optionally, advanced encryption and password protection can be added.</li>
      <li>Collects and stores all possible data from past days. Enough to be able to reconstruct each day in your memory.</li>
      <li>Helps plan the future based on past experience.</li>
      <li>AI tools analyze behavior patterns and highlight areas for improvement.</li>
      <li>Gradually immerses you in the experience by introducing new practices and tools through a modular interface.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  <section>
    <h2>1. Structure and data visualization</h2>
    <p>A life-based structure supports and extends your natural memory.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>A year, month, and week layout that lets you navigate past dates and keeps the finiteness of life in view.</li>
      <li>A daily structure with meta-data (location, weather), templates for different day types (work, weekend, vacation), weekly reflection prompts, habits, tasks, and events.</li>
      <li>A semantic graph that links entries by tags, location, mood, and record type.</li>
      <li>A viewing mode with an auto-generated one-sentence summary of the day.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  <section>
    <h2>2. Daily journaling practice</h2>
    <p>Writing every day is one of the most powerful habits you can build. It fuels growth and keeps your head clear.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Instant capture — open the app and start writing right away.</li>
      <li>Voice input with speech recognition.</li>
      <li>Scanning and recognizing handwritten notes from paper notebooks.</li>
      <li>An inbox for fast capture: write first, then sort. Turn a note into a journal entry, a task, or an event.</li>
      <li>A universal note template (entry type, life area, photo, tag, mood, a 1–10 rating, and a reflection prompt).</li>
      <li>An emotion tracker built into each note, because every emotion is a response to something in your environment.</li>
      <li>Baseline reset tools (breathing exercises and meditations for the moments when writing isn’t enough).</li>
      <li>Review and reflection, log key moments from past years, months, and days.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  <section>
    <h2>3. Planning</h2>
    <p>Planning the future works best when it’s grounded in a long-term vision and the progress you’ve already made. It links all the elements together top to bottom.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Life vision for 3, 5, and 10 years.</li>
      <li>Your ideal future day in details.</li>
      <li>Key life areas.</li>
      <li>A past year review.</li>
      <li>Goals for the year, quarter, and month.</li>
      <li>Tasks for weekly sprints and for today.</li>
      <li>A nightly mind-dump to clear your head and outline tomorrow’s priorities.</li>
      <li>Backlogs for projects and life areas.</li>
      <li>Daily habits connected to your goals and key life areas.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  <section>
    <h2>4. Calendar</h2>
    <p>It shows the actual time you need to make your plans real. If it’s not on the calendar, it won't happen.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Past events and meetings.</li>
      <li>Upcoming events and meetings.</li>
      <li>Time blocks for deep work, training, recovery, and social time.</li>
      <li>Scheduling links for sharing with people.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  <section>
    <h2>5. Dashboard and analytics</h2>
    <p>A bit of gamification around your core metrics helps you stay aware of your progress, and gives you the motivation to keep going.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>A tree of key metrics (quality of life, longevity, productive work).</li>
      <li>Goal-achievement progress.</li>
      <li>Key memories for this day (from one, two, or five years ago).</li>
      <li>Stats across mood, location, events, and meetings.</li>
      <li>Smart search that understands the semantics of your query.</li>
      <li>A profile with all settings.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  <section>
    <h2>6. AI assistant</h2>
    <p>The system analyzes your journal entries and reveals repeating behavior patterns you might be missing.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Learns from your data and the contexts that matter to you.</li>
      <li>Identifies behavioral patterns.</li>
      <li>Offers guidance to help you reach your goals.</li>
      <li>Supports reflective, therapeutic-style conversations.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  <section>
    <h2>7. Close relationships</h2>
    <p>Your closest connections are the most important part of your life. It makes sense to plan intentionally so those connections keep getting deeper.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Shared notes about events (collective journal entries with friends).</li>
      <li>A visual overview of friends’ moods.</li>
      <li>Shared plans, friends can see your calendar, available time slots, and location.</li>
      <li>A viral-friendly invite flow for bringing people into the product.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  <section>
    <h2>8. Educational layer</h2>
    <p>The experience unfolds step by step so you don't get overwhelmed. The product guides you through each practice and teaches you how to use it in your life.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>You start with daily writing and basic metrics.</li>
      <li>Every new layer builds on the previous one.</li>
      <li>A course on holistic life design that delivers all the tools in a concise, engaging way.</li>
      <li>Discovery and synthesis of materials based on your current needs, delivered in a podcast-style format.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  <section>
    <h2>Monetization</h2>
    <p>Simple daily writing as the core practice is always free. A subscription unlocks all advanced features, supports ongoing development, and keeps the vision moving forward.</p>
  </section>
